frf5.name: frf5
frf5.contactinfo: Postal: FORE Systems, Inc. 1000 FORE Drive Warrendale, PA 15086-7502 USA Tel: +1 724-742-4444 Email: info@fore.com Web: http://www.fore.com
frf5.description: This MIB module defines FR/ATM interworking tables. It gives the means to create/remove a FR/ATM interworking connection and provides statistics at the connection level.

frf5ConnTable.name: frf5ConnTable
frf5ConnTable.description: Table of cross connections between the frame relay and ATM Fabric connections

frf5ConnEntry.name: frf5ConnEntry
frf5ConnEntry.description: Entry in the frame relay/atm netmod crossconnect table

frf5ConnFrServiceIfIndex.name: frf5ConnFrServiceIfIndex
frf5ConnFrServiceIfIndex.description: Interface index of the Frame Relay service this connection exists on

frf5ConnDlci.name: frf5ConnDlci
frf5ConnDlci.description: DLCI of this connection on the frame relay service

frf5ConnFrsscsDlci.name: frf5ConnFrsscsDlci
frf5ConnFrsscsDlci.description: FR SSCS DLCI of this connection which will be multiplexed on a ATM PVC

frf5ConnFabServiceIfIndex.name: frf5ConnFabServiceIfIndex
frf5ConnFabServiceIfIndex.description: This is the IfIndex associated with the fabric pseudo atm service this connection is mapped to by the agent when this Frame Relay connection is created.

frf5ConnFabAtmIf.name: frf5ConnFabAtmIf
frf5ConnFabAtmIf.description: This is the fabric ATM interface of the ATM connection this frame relay/ATM connection is mapped to by the agent when this row is created. This variable can be set only for dangling connections.

frf5ConnFabVpi.name: frf5ConnFabVpi
frf5ConnFabVpi.description: This is the fabric VPI (equivalent to ivpi) of the ATM connection this frame relay/ATM connection is mapped to by the agent when this row is created. This VPI will be used to establish a connection across the switching fabric by means of the FORE-switch MIB. This variable can be set only for dangling connections.

frf5ConnFabVci.name: frf5ConnFabVci
frf5ConnFabVci.description: This is the fabric VCI (equivalent to ivci) of the ATM connection this frame relay connection is mapped to by the agent when this row is created. This VCI will be used to establish a connection across the switching fabric by means of the FORE-switch MIB. This variable can be set only for dangling connections.

frf5ConnRowStatus.name: frf5ConnRowStatus
frf5ConnRowStatus.description: This object is used for dynamic creation of entries in this table and all frame relay connection level tables. This object is also used to delete existing connection rows.

frf5ConnProfileEpdPpdIndex.name: frf5ConnProfileEpdPpdIndex
frf5ConnProfileEpdPpdIndex.description: The index of the EpdPpd Controller profile.

frf5ConnAtmAddrType.name: frf5ConnAtmAddrType
frf5ConnAtmAddrType.description: Defines the address format of the ATM Service User end point

frf5ConnAtmAddress.name: frf5ConnAtmAddress
frf5ConnAtmAddress.description: The destination ATM address to which this Virtual Circuit is connected.

frf5ConnAtmSubAddrType.name: frf5ConnAtmSubAddrType
frf5ConnAtmSubAddrType.description: Defines the sub-address format of the ATM Service User end point

frf5ConnAtmSubAddress.name: frf5ConnAtmSubAddress
frf5ConnAtmSubAddress.description: The destination ATM subaddress to which this Virtual Circuit is connected.

frf5ConnFrAddrType.name: frf5ConnFrAddrType
frf5ConnFrAddrType.description: Defines the frame relay address format of the Frame Relay Service User end point

frf5ConnFrAddress.name: frf5ConnFrAddress
frf5ConnFrAddress.description: The address to which the Frame Relay DLCI is connected.

frf5ConnAdminStatus.name: frf5ConnAdminStatus
frf5ConnAdminStatus.description: Indicates whether the particular virtual circuit is operational.

frf5ConnOperStatus.name: frf5ConnOperStatus
frf5ConnOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the interworking connection

frf5ConnCreationTime.name: frf5ConnCreationTime
frf5ConnCreationTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the virtual circuit was created

frf5ConnTimeChange.name: frf5ConnTimeChange
frf5ConnTimeChange.description: The value of sysUpTime (MIB II) when last there was a change in the virtual circuit state

frf5extDlcmiTable.name: frf5extDlcmiTable
frf5extDlcmiTable.description: The Parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface corresponding to a given ifEntry. These parameters are logical extensions to those contained within the object frDlcmiTable in RFC1315.

frf5extDlcmiEntry.name: frf5extDlcmiEntry
frf5extDlcmiEntry.description: The Parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface.

frf5extDlmciAtmIf.name: frf5extDlmciAtmIf
frf5extDlmciAtmIf.description: The Atm interface index corresponds to the port. This is also the index of the portTable.

frf5extDlcmiAtmVpi.name: frf5extDlcmiAtmVpi
frf5extDlcmiAtmVpi.description: VPI of the ATM VCC on which FR DLCIs are multiplexed

frf5extDlcmiAtmVci.name: frf5extDlcmiAtmVci
frf5extDlcmiAtmVci.description: VCI of the ATM VCC on which FR DLCIs are multiplexed

frf5extDlcmiProfileLmiIndex.name: frf5extDlcmiProfileLmiIndex
frf5extDlcmiProfileLmiIndex.description: Index for the LMI profile for this ATM VCC.

frf5extDlcmiProfileFrf5Index.name: frf5extDlcmiProfileFrf5Index
frf5extDlcmiProfileFrf5Index.description: Index for the FRF5 profile, in the fore-profile.mib.

frf5extDlcmiStatsMonitor.name: frf5extDlcmiStatsMonitor
frf5extDlcmiStatsMonitor.description: This object specifies whether statistics (ATM VCC and FR DLCI statistics) are to be counted at an ATM VCC level. When the state changes from enabled to disabled, all the related statistics will be frozen at their current value. When the state changes from disabled to enabled, all related statistics will be reset (zeroed). Note that this Monitor is overridden by the netmod level nmFramStatsMonitor. Refer to fore-fram.mib for more details.

frf5extDlcmiStatsEnabledTimeStamp.name: frf5extDlcmiStatsEnabledTimeStamp
frf5extDlcmiStatsEnabledTimeStamp.description: This object reflects the point in time, with reference to sysUpTime, either when frf5extDlcmiStatsMonitor is set to enabled or when nmFramStatsMonitor is set to enabled. The time will reflect the last StatsMonitor to be enabled. The timestamp provides a starting timestamp for the current statistics that are being counted.

frf5extDlcmiLmiDlci.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiDlci
frf5extDlcmiLmiDlci.description: The dlci upon which LMI traffic will be broadcast. If Q933-AnnexA=0, otherwise STRATACOM=1023.

frf5extDlcmiLmiFlowControl.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiFlowControl
frf5extDlcmiLmiFlowControl.description: Specifies whether STRATACOM LMI based (R-bit) notification performs flow control for the Circuits on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiBandwidthControl.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiBandwidthControl
frf5extDlcmiLmiBandwidthControl.description: Specifies whether STRATACOM LMI based CIR notification affects the CIR flow control parameters for the connections on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiRxAbortedFrames.name: frf5extDlcmiRxAbortedFrames
frf5extDlcmiRxAbortedFrames.description: The number of aborted frames received on this Frame Relay logical interface. A frame is considered aborted after receiving 7 or more continuous ones.

frf5extDlcmiRcvCrcErrors.name: frf5extDlcmiRcvCrcErrors
frf5extDlcmiRcvCrcErrors.description: Specifies the number of frames receive with CRC errors on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiRcvShortFrames.name: frf5extDlcmiRcvShortFrames
frf5extDlcmiRcvShortFrames.description: The number of frames containing less than 5 octets received on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiRcvLongFrames.name: frf5extDlcmiRcvLongFrames
frf5extDlcmiRcvLongFrames.description: The number of frames containing greater than 8191 octets received on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiRcvInvalidDLCI.name: frf5extDlcmiRcvInvalidDLCI
frf5extDlcmiRcvInvalidDLCI.description: The number of frames with an invalid DLCI received on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiRcvUnknownErrs.name: frf5extDlcmiRcvUnknownErrs
frf5extDlcmiRcvUnknownErrs.description: The number of frames with other errors received on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiTxStatusResponses.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiTxStatusResponses
frf5extDlcmiLmiTxStatusResponses.description: Number of STATUS messages transmitted on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusResponses.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusResponses
frf5extDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusResponses.description: Number of STATUS messages with full status Information Element transmitted on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiTxStatusEnquiries.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiTxStatusEnquiries
frf5extDlcmiLmiTxStatusEnquiries.description: Number of STATUS ENQUIRY messages transmitted on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusEnquiries.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusEnquiries
frf5extDlcmiLmiTxFullStatusEnquiries.description: Number of STATUS ENQUIRY messages with full status Information Element transmitted on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiRxStatusResponses.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiRxStatusResponses
frf5extDlcmiLmiRxStatusResponses.description: Number of STATUS messages received on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusResponses.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusResponses
frf5extDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusResponses.description: Number of STATUS messages with full status Information Element received on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiRxStatusEnquiries.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiRxStatusEnquiries
frf5extDlcmiLmiRxStatusEnquiries.description: Number of STATUS messages received on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusEnquiries.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusEnquiries
frf5extDlcmiLmiRxFullStatusEnquiries.description: Number of STATUS ENQUIRY messages with full status Information Element receive on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiUnknownMessagesRcvd.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiUnknownMessagesRcvd
frf5extDlcmiLmiUnknownMessagesRcvd.description: Number of Unknown LMI messages received on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiStatusLostSequences.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiStatusLostSequences
frf5extDlcmiLmiStatusLostSequences.description: The total number of times a loss of sequencing in received STATUS messages was detected on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiStatusEnqLostSequences.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiStatusEnqLostSequences
frf5extDlcmiLmiStatusEnqLostSequences.description: The total number of times a loss of sequencing in received STATUS ENQUIRY messages was detected on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiMissingStatEnquiries.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiMissingStatEnquiries
frf5extDlcmiLmiMissingStatEnquiries.description: The number of times an expected STATUS ENQUIRY message was not received within the expected time on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiUnexpectedPVCStatMsg.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiUnexpectedPVCStatMsg
frf5extDlcmiLmiUnexpectedPVCStatMsg.description: The number of LMI messages that were received with unexpected PVC STATUS Information Element on this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiUnexpectedDLCI.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiUnexpectedDLCI
frf5extDlcmiLmiUnexpectedDLCI.description: The number of STATUS messages received with unconfigured DLCI

frf5extDlcmiLmiStatEnqRatePlus.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiStatEnqRatePlus
frf5extDlcmiLmiStatEnqRatePlus.description: The number of times the STATUS ENQUIRY message was received more frequently than expected. For STRATACOM only

frf5extDlcmiLmiInvInfoFrame.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiInvInfoFrame
frf5extDlcmiLmiInvInfoFrame.description: The number of times an LMI message was received with information type not equal to unnumbered information type.

frf5extDlcmiLmiInvFrameHdr.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiInvFrameHdr
frf5extDlcmiLmiInvFrameHdr.description: The number of LMI frames received with error in the header bits.

frf5extDlcmiLmiNoIERepType.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiNoIERepType
frf5extDlcmiLmiNoIERepType.description: The number of times an LMI frame was received with missing Report Type Information Element

frf5extDlcmiLmiNoIEKeepAlive.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiNoIEKeepAlive
frf5extDlcmiLmiNoIEKeepAlive.description: The number of times an LMI frame was received with missing Link Integrity Verification Information Element.

frf5extDlcmiLmiMissingResponses.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiMissingResponses
frf5extDlcmiLmiMissingResponses.description: The total number of times a timeout occurred without receiving a response to an LMI request by this interface.

frf5extDlcmiLmiUnsuppIERcvd.name: frf5extDlcmiLmiUnsuppIERcvd
frf5extDlcmiLmiUnsuppIERcvd.description: The number of LMI messages received with unknown Information Element.

frf5extDlcmiDlcis.name: frf5extDlcmiDlcis
frf5extDlcmiDlcis.description: The number of permanent DLCIs established on this ATM logical interface

frf5extDlcmiUserLinkRelErrors.name: frf5extDlcmiUserLinkRelErrors
frf5extDlcmiUserLinkRelErrors.description: The number of user-side local in-channel signalling link reliability errors (i.e., non- receipt of Status/Status Enquiry messages or invalid sequence numbers in a Link Integrity Verification Information Element) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing user-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName.

frf5extDlcmiUserProtErrors.name: frf5extDlcmiUserProtErrors
frf5extDlcmiUserProtErrors.description: The number of user-side local in-channel signalling protocol errors (i.e., protocol discriminator, message type, call reference, and mandatory information element errors) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing user-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName.

frf5extDlcmiUserChanInactive.name: frf5extDlcmiUserChanInactive
frf5extDlcmiUserChanInactive.description: The number of times the user-side channel was declared inactive (i.e., N392 errors in N393 events) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing user-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName.

frf5extDlcmiNetLinkRelErrors.name: frf5extDlcmiNetLinkRelErrors
frf5extDlcmiNetLinkRelErrors.description: The number of network-side local in-channel signalling link reliability errors (i.e., non- receipt of Status/Status Enquiry messages or invalid sequence numbers in a Link Integrity Verification Information Element) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing network-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName.

frf5extDlcmiNetProtErrors.name: frf5extDlcmiNetProtErrors
frf5extDlcmiNetProtErrors.description: The number of network-side local in-channel signalling protocol errors (i.e., protocol discriminator, message type, call reference, and mandatory information element errors) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing network-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName.

frf5extDlcmiNetChanInactive.name: frf5extDlcmiNetChanInactive
frf5extDlcmiNetChanInactive.description: The number of times the network-side channel was declared inactive (i.e., N392 errors in N393 events) for this UNI/NNI logical port. If the logical port is not performing network-side procedures, then this value is equal to noSuchName.

frf5extDlcmiRootService.name: frf5extDlcmiRootService
frf5extDlcmiRootService.description: The service ifindex of the first connection belonging to this VCC.

frf5extDlcmiRootDlci.name: frf5extDlcmiRootDlci
frf5extDlcmiRootDlci.description: The dlci of the first connection belonging to this VCC.
